This somehow makes me think of what <a href="http://www.fceux.com/web/help/fceux.html?CodeDataLogger.html" class="postlink">FCEUX CDL files</a> were made for, in combination with <a href="http://www.fceux.com/web/help/fceux.html" class="postlink">FCEUX Bookmarks</a>.<br /><br />Also, an interactive disassembler for 6502 is already available in the form of <a href="https://www.hex-rays.com/products/ida/" class="postlink">IDA Pro</a>, but of course the issue there is that there's no NES emulator integration + memory mapped register knowledge.  Honestly, for NES stuff an interactive disassembler is mainly useful when there's an emulator tied to it in real-time (same goes for Apple II stuff, etc.).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Sun Jul 06, 2014 2:48 pm</p><hr />
